        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 15 at 3:29PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 329 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Check, or 7 miles southwest of Copper Hill, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Rocky Mount...
Floyd...
Boones Mill...
Pilot...
Copper Hill...
Ferrum...
and Bent Mountain.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
